The PCN-PEO slurry was doctor-bladed onto the surface of a PTFE plate and then placed in a vacuum oven and dried at 50 °C for 12 h. The PCN-PEO electrolyte membrane can be obtained when the temperature dropped to room temperature. The ionic conductivities of PCN-PEO electrolyte membrane were measured by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) of SS/electrolyte/SS blocking cell from 1 MHz to 0.1 Hz at room temperature. And the ionic conductivity was calculated based on the Eq. S1:S1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
